cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on optimizing content delivery and improving users' QoE in Cloud-based RAN systems, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed caching framework utilizes cloud infrastructure and shared computing resources, which is a key aspect of distributed and cluster computing. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper introduces a delay cost model and proposes a cache management strategy, which involves algorithmic optimization and data structure management. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The caching strategy proposed in the paper aims to minimize network costs and improve QoE, which can be seen as a control problem in systems engineering. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves optimizing content delivery and cache placement, which can be viewed as an information theory problem related to data transmission and storage.
